    "sections": [
      {
        "trade": "Prep & Testing",
        "lines": [
          "Pull city permit / verify permit requirement for cosmetic ceiling scrape work with local building department.",
          "Test ceiling texture for asbestos (house built 1982, pre-1990) — pull bulk sample per room/texture batch and send to accredited lab; do not scrape, sand, or wet ceiling before results are back.",
          "In case of asbestos: house must be cleared 100% to a pod outside the house before abatement crew removes the ceiling; painter completes the job and moves furniture back once abatement crew has finished.",
          "Remove furniture as needed.",
          "Cover all working areas with plastics.",
          "Cover all floors."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Ceiling – Popcorn Removal",
        "lines": [
          "Spray ceiling with water to moist the surface.",
          "Scrape the moist surface of the ceiling.",
          "Refresh all plastics cover to new after popcorn removal and re-cover the job site.",
          "Fix cracks and openings in the ceiling.",
          "Apply taping and plaster as needed.",
          "Apply texture: smooth or texture (customer will choose).",
          "Sand new plaster."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Paint – Interior (Ceilings & Walls)",
        "lines": [
          "Prepare all working areas as needed.",
          "Open cracks wider and fill up cracks on walls.",
          "Fix and patch all walls.",
          "Sand walls.",
          "Apply primer and 2 coats of paint on ceilings.",
          "Apply primer and 2 coats of paint on walls.",
          "Paint trim around walls/baseboards: apply primer and 2 coats of paint.",
          "Place everything back to pre-existing state."
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Clean Up",
        "lines": [
          "Remove all plastics and clean job site.",
          "Haul away trash."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "notes": [
      "House built 1982 (pre-1990): asbestos survey required before ceiling disturbance per AQMD Rule 1403; job can proceed room-by-room with occupants remaining in the house only if the test comes back negative.",
      "Smooth vs. textured ceiling finish to be confirmed with customer before plaster/texture step.",
      "Paint brand/tier (Behr, Sherwin-Williams, Dunn-Edwards, Benjamin Moore) and sheen per room to be confirmed with customer."
